00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:30.050
get a much better experience.

00:04:30.050 --> 00:04:35.560
And we get a much smoother
scrolling experience going on.

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:36.150
PAUL KINLAN: Yeah.

00:04:36.150 --> 00:04:38.610
So everyone knows, this is
like basically a threaded

00:04:38.610 --> 00:04:39.250
compositor now.

00:04:39.250 --> 00:04:42.255
So in the past, essentially,
paints and everything used to

00:04:42.255 --> 00:04:44.370
block the--

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:46.730
if you did a paint and then a
render, it would block the

00:04:46.730 --> 00:04:49.010
actual browser for that time.

00:04:49.010 --> 00:04:49.690
And now it doesn't.

00:04:49.690 --> 00:04:50.830
It's on a completely
separate thread.

00:04:50.830 --> 00:04:53.820
Internally, we called it
imple-side threading, or

00:04:53.820 --> 00:04:55.000
imple-side painting,
I'm sorry.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:56.660
It's like a completely
obtuse name.

00:04:56.660 --> 00:04:58.910
But essentially, what it does
is exactly what Pete just

00:04:58.910 --> 00:05:00.890
described, where you'll
do a scroll.

00:05:00.890 --> 00:05:03.510
And we've got low resolution
versions of the page that's

00:05:03.510 --> 00:05:06.010
all rendered out anyway.

00:05:06.010 --> 00:05:08.190
We've got low resolution
versions of the page which we

00:05:08.190 --> 00:05:09.340
can quickly show to the user.

00:05:09.340 --> 00:05:12.020
And then when the scrolling
stops, we swap that out.

00:05:12.020 --> 00:05:14.395
And we give it back to the
user in full, high res.

00:05:14.395 --> 00:05:16.490
And we think this is a better
way of doing it, because

00:05:16.490 --> 00:05:18.630
that's one of the worst things
that we have at the moment on

00:05:18.630 --> 00:05:22.660
the mobile web, is if you
scroll, you lose track of

00:05:22.660 --> 00:05:23.420
everything.

00:05:23.420 --> 00:05:27.330
The app would try to paint,
but the user wouldn't see

00:05:27.330 --> 00:05:29.570
anything, because we
couldn't keep up.

00:05:29.570 --> 00:05:32.240
And this is a big improvement
for the way that you develop

00:05:32.240 --> 00:05:34.050
apps, or at least the
way that your users

00:05:34.050 --> 00:05:36.070
see your site snaps.

00:05:36.070 --> 00:05:36.630
PETE LEPAGE: Yeah.

00:05:36.630 --> 00:05:37.700
