00:06:10.690 --> 00:06:13.200
But I think it's basically a
benefit of having the threaded

00:06:13.200 --> 00:06:14.190
compositor now.

00:06:14.190 --> 00:06:16.830
The interesting thing, and we
found this out a couple of

00:06:16.830 --> 00:06:21.260
weeks ago, is that we always
have this like 300 millisecond

00:06:21.260 --> 00:06:22.543
delay on clicks.

00:06:22.543 --> 00:06:24.800
You click a link, or
click anything.

00:06:24.800 --> 00:06:26.560
Obviously, it needs to work out
whether you're going to

00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:28.270
try to do another
type of gesture.

00:06:28.270 --> 00:06:30.930
And that whole subsystem's been
starting to be improved.

00:06:30.930 --> 00:06:33.420
But the interesting thing is if
you have your viewport set,

00:06:33.420 --> 00:06:36.050
which we might talk about
viewport today, but we

00:06:36.050 --> 00:06:38.093
probably have a whole dedicated
session for

00:06:38.093 --> 00:06:39.000
viewports in the future.

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.240
